# Component Patterns

## Architecture

- `App.tsx` is the orchestrator: state, data loaders, event handlers only. No UI markup for tab contents.
- Each tab lives in `components/tabs/<Name>Tab.tsx` and receives data/callbacks via props.
- Reusable UI primitives live in `components/shared/` (Card, Badge, Toggle, StatBox, etc.).
- Types are centralized in `types.ts`. Hooks in `hooks/`.

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase (`StatBox.tsx`, `McpTab.tsx`)
- Props interfaces: `<ComponentName>Props`
- Event handler props: `on<Action>` (e.g. `onSaveConfig`, `onRefresh`)

## Shared Components API

- `Card`: title (required), headerRight (optional), children
- `PageHeader`: title, description (optional), children (action buttons)
- `EmptyState`: title, description, icon (SVG), variant ("default" | "error" | "hero"), action
- `StatBox`: label, value, icon, description, colorClass, variant ("stat" | "info")
- `Badge`: variant ("pending" | "approved" | "denied" | "info"), children
- `Toggle`: checked, onChange, label (for accessibility)
- `ListItemCard`: badge, title, meta, actions

## User-Facing Text

- Use plain language, not developer jargon
- Tab names: Dashboard, Configuration, Pending Actions, IDE Protection
- Button labels: "Protect" (not "Wrap"), "Remove" (not "Unwrap")
- Badge labels: "Protected" / "Unprotected" (not "wrapped" / "unwrapped")
- Always include a description prop on PageHeader explaining what the tab does
